title: Caffe2: Two entries of external_input "data_0" in mnist_predict_net.pbtxt file
body_html:
After training mnist model in caffe2 I found there are two entries of external_input "data_0" in mnist predict_net file. I think it should only have one entry so does any one know how this external_input entries are generated while training model.

I have attached the mnist .pbtxt file here.
mnist_predict_net.pbtxt.zip

body:
After training mnist model in caffe2 I found there are two entries of external_input "data_0" in mnist predict_net file. I think it should only have one entry so does any one know how this external_input entries are generated while training model.

I have attached the mnist .pbtxt file here.
